</P>
<P>
   CATFISH _ Some believe the next world-record flathead catfish _
the current record is 93 pounds _ will come from the Altamaha River
in Southeast Georgia. But there has been some controversy. The fish
was illegally introduced in the Altamaha several years back, and
despite contentions by some that the flathead is ruining the
habitat for other species, anglers go out regularly in search of a
trophy. A tournament based in Jesup on Sept. 12-13 provides the
backdrop for flathead fever. (Bernarde, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 25'.
</P>
